1
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:18,167
Turns out, Wilberto's a hero.

2
00:00:18,300 --> 00:00:21,567
Awesome! At least we're
friends with a hero, right?

3
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:24,667
Wow, that's a pretty
bright smile, bestie.

4
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:28,067
You're getting really
comfortable around Wilberto.

5
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,767
I just see him
a bit differently

6
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:32,267
after learning about his past.

7
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:35,433
I'm worried my sister
will get upset at me again.

8
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,133
Oh, come on!

9
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:39,967
Leave it to me.

10
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:41,400
What if...

11
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:44,700
we bring her something
to ease the tension?

12
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:49,100
There are more perverts
in this day and age.

13
00:00:49,233 --> 00:00:51,233
Good thing you got some
boxing skills, chica!

14
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:54,067
Thank you so much
for the effort.

15
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:57,633
If I was alive, I would've
done it again and again.

16
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:01,167
Hey! Are you just going
to stare at each other,

17
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:03,100
or are we visiting Nadia?

18
00:01:03,233 --> 00:01:04,867
- I apologize.
- You missed her house, man!

19
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,100
This is it.

20
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:08,233
We have the option
to open her third eye.

21
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:10,233
I've got my healing oil.

22
00:01:11,033 --> 00:01:12,367
I've given it
consideration, Emma.

23
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:13,900
Oh, come on!

24
00:01:14,033 --> 00:01:15,833
Don't worry!

25
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:20,467
Emma, plus Jaja,
at your service.

26
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,633
Let me guess.

27
00:01:21,767 --> 00:01:22,967
You have a third eye,

28
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,667
and you're with
Grandpa Wilberto right now.

29
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:26,200
- Correct!
- That's right!

30
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:27,700
- Wait!
- [DOOR SLAMS]

31
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:30,167
Are you alright?

32
00:01:32,733 --> 00:01:37,900
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:01:38,033 --> 00:01:39,367
Are we on?

34
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:41,833
What?

35
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:44,500
She said you're on now, man!

36
00:01:46,033 --> 00:01:47,533
Idiot!

37
00:01:47,667 --> 00:01:49,633
Are we on with the plan?

38
00:01:49,767 --> 00:01:51,333
[JAJA] Bert!

39
00:01:51,467 --> 00:01:52,333
[WHINES]

40
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:55,200
We don't mean any harm!

41
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:57,433
Bert!

42
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:02,033
Tell Bert I've done this
time and again.

43
00:02:03,067 --> 00:02:06,200
Is it not proof enough that
I wish to speak with my sister?

44
00:02:08,533 --> 00:02:12,033
Treb is serious about this!
I mean, Wilberto!

45
00:02:12,167 --> 00:02:14,100
He's sent lots of people
here before,

46
00:02:14,267 --> 00:02:15,833
so he could reach out.

47
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:17,900
I don't want to disobey Grandma!

48
00:02:18,033 --> 00:02:20,200
I'm just respecting her wishes!

49
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:23,433
Tell him I shall not rest.
I'll do all that I must.

50
00:02:23,567 --> 00:02:25,733
He knows I speak the truth!

51
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:28,867
I've proved it so many times to
the people who can see me too.

52
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:33,233
He said he's not going to stop
and you know it's the truth!

53
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:34,800
Tell him he's being annoying!

54
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:37,967
He's revealed so many
family secrets to strangers

55
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:39,733
just to prove his point!

56
00:02:39,867 --> 00:02:41,500
I'm still his grandfather!

57
00:02:41,633 --> 00:02:43,833
Could you please ask him
to show some respect?

58
00:02:43,967 --> 00:02:45,733
He's that desperate, Bert!

59
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,333
He wants to fulfill
his promises to his sister.

60
00:02:50,567 --> 00:02:53,133
Don't you want your grandpa's
soul to rest in peace?

61
00:02:53,267 --> 00:02:57,267
He only wants to apologize!
Is that so wrong?

62
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:03,800
Even if he's no longer here,
he's still trying to reach out.

63
00:03:03,933 --> 00:03:05,533
You know, Bert,

64
00:03:05,667 --> 00:03:08,433
not everyone
gets a chance like this.

65
00:03:08,567 --> 00:03:12,433
Even the living
waste every chance

66
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,500
while they're still alive,

67
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:17,367
only to regret it
when it's too late.

68
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,700
So please, don't deny him
this closure, Bert.

69
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,500
Even death won't stop him

70
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:27,667
from trying
to make things right.

71
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:34,667
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

72
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:41,833
Sorry.

73
00:03:51,467 --> 00:03:54,233
[MUSIC BECOMES CHEERY]

74
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,200
- [SQUEALS]
- Finally!

75
00:03:57,800 --> 00:04:00,667
Tell him thank you.
I won't waste this chance.

76
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:04,133
He says thank you.
He won't waste this chance.

77
00:04:04,267 --> 00:04:05,333
And...

78
00:04:06,167 --> 00:04:09,533
he's asking for some respect
since he's still your grandpa.

79
00:04:12,067 --> 00:04:14,000
Okay. Come in.

80
00:04:14,133 --> 00:04:15,600
[JAJA] Yeah!

81
00:04:15,733 --> 00:04:17,367
- [JAJA] Wow.
- [EMMA] Thanks!

82
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,733
[JAJA]
What a fancy house!

83
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:28,600
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

84
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:59,133
[EMMA]
Girlypop, this is it.

85
00:04:59,267 --> 00:05:02,867
What a huge, fancy house.

86
00:05:03,033 --> 00:05:04,167
Wow.

87
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:06,633
- Go ahead and take your seats.
- Thanks.

88
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:09,367
We'll wait for your grandma
until she's ready.

89
00:05:11,100 --> 00:05:12,900
Wow.

90
00:05:13,033 --> 00:05:15,033
Why did he head to the kitchen?

91
00:05:15,167 --> 00:05:16,733
My sister's room
is on the upper floor.

92
00:05:17,933 --> 00:05:19,433
Chill out.

93
00:05:19,567 --> 00:05:21,600
Maybe he's just
grabbing some food.

94
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:24,900
[EMMA] Perfect timing!
I'm actually kind of hungry.

95
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:26,767
[CLICKS TONGUE]

96
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:30,200
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

97
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:31,533
Wow.

98
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:35,567
Miss Nadia sure built
a pretty huge family.

99
00:05:35,733 --> 00:05:37,400
- You're right.
- Such a shame, man.

100
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:38,900
You didn't get to know them.

101
00:05:40,033 --> 00:05:41,067
What's taking so long?

102
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:44,500
Why isn't there even a single
old photo of you here?

103
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:48,400
They must have been destroyed
during the war, you know.

104
00:05:48,533 --> 00:05:51,067
No, I feel there's some
kind of family drama or--

105
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:56,533
- Sorry, Treb. Sorry.
- Watch your mouth, girl.

106
00:05:56,667 --> 00:05:58,033
Well, you're right, Emma.

107
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,633
Her resentment runs so deep...

108
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:09,033
that I've nearly been
forgotten in our family.

109
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:12,467
Hey!

110
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,200
What's wrong with you?!

111
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:16,233
You two will reconcile,
of course!

112
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:18,367
We're manifesting that,
right guys?

113
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,933
- Yes!
- We're not giving up now.

114
00:06:20,067 --> 00:06:22,267
- True! Think positive.
- Think positive!

115
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:25,067
- Think positive, guys.
- Cheer up! Come on.

116
00:06:26,867 --> 00:06:28,400
Have some snacks.

117
00:06:28,533 --> 00:06:30,600
- Perfect timing.
- Thank you so much.

118
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:32,333
- Thank you!
- Thanks.

119
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:34,667
That looks good!

120
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:40,367
Did he say if I can
talk to her already?

121
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:43,733
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

122
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:45,500
Uh, Bert?

123
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:47,967
Is your grandma ready?

124
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:50,333
Uh, I'll just ask Dad.

125
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:51,800
Heard that?

126
00:06:53,133 --> 00:06:54,467
Why does he have to ask?

127
00:06:54,600 --> 00:07:00,300
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:07:00,433 --> 00:07:01,767
Bert?

129
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,767
He's asking why you need
to check with your dad.

130
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:06,933
Grandpa's messengers
are usually not allowed in here.

131
00:07:07,067 --> 00:07:08,400
Got your answer?

132
00:07:08,533 --> 00:07:09,733
Can you stop asking already?

133
00:07:09,867 --> 00:07:12,767
I really want to bite
into this biscuit.

134
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:15,667
I don't need anyone's
permission to talk to Nadia!

135
00:07:16,467 --> 00:07:17,600
Hey, wait!

136
00:07:17,733 --> 00:07:19,067
[EMMA]
He has a point though.

137
00:07:19,867 --> 00:07:21,100
No, no! No!

138
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,133
He's already upstairs!

139
00:07:23,267 --> 00:07:25,033
- He needs his translator!
- No!

140
00:07:25,167 --> 00:07:26,767
No, you can't go upstairs!

141
00:07:29,767 --> 00:07:32,000
So rude! He had
to use English on me!

142
00:07:33,633 --> 00:07:36,733
- [MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]
- [EKG BEEPING]

143
00:07:36,867 --> 00:07:39,667
Nadia! Nadia!

144
00:07:40,367 --> 00:07:41,633
Oh my gosh.

145
00:07:42,933 --> 00:07:43,867
That's Treb.

146
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,100
Nadia!

147
00:07:48,033 --> 00:07:49,200
Nadia...

148
00:07:51,167 --> 00:07:52,433
Nadia.

149
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,067
Nadia.

150
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:01,433
Nadia...

151
00:08:03,633 --> 00:08:06,600
Girl, go to him.
I'll stay here and wait for you!

152
00:08:09,167 --> 00:08:10,067
Yes, Dad?

153
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,200
- Nadia...
- They didn't ask for anything.

154
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:14,433
But okay, I'll tell them to go.

155
00:08:15,667 --> 00:08:17,467
The woman said Grandpa's
here upstairs.

156
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,733
I don't know.
I can't feel anything.

157
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:23,933
Nadia...

158
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:26,900
[BERT]
Hold on, Dad.

159
00:08:27,033 --> 00:08:29,000
- Why are you here?
- Oh my god.

160
00:08:31,467 --> 00:08:33,867
Please, let them talk.

161
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:36,533
How can they talk
if Grandma's unconscious?

162
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:41,033
N-Nadia, I beg you,
wake up.

163
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:43,000
Your big brother's here.

164
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:44,333
Nadia.

165
00:08:44,467 --> 00:08:46,067
Her immune system's weak.

166
00:08:47,633 --> 00:08:48,633
Please get out.

167
00:08:48,767 --> 00:08:50,800
If her condition gets worse,
it's your fault.

168
00:08:50,933 --> 00:08:57,967
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:00,900
Leave.

170
00:09:07,267 --> 00:09:14,100
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:16,533
[SNIFFLES]

172
00:09:17,567 --> 00:09:18,967
Nadia...

173
00:09:19,733 --> 00:09:21,533
Bert, please!

174
00:09:21,667 --> 00:09:24,400
- Just let us stay here.
- No!

175
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:25,567
Sorry!

176
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:27,400
I just went up
because Treb shouted.

177
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:29,600
- I didn't hear it.
- Exactly!

178
00:09:29,733 --> 00:09:31,400
That's why they need us there.

179
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:33,400
- Girl, what happened?
- Get out.

180
00:09:33,533 --> 00:09:35,400
- What?
- Leave!

181
00:09:35,533 --> 00:09:36,700
[HUFFS]

182
00:09:42,567 --> 00:09:44,633
We need to get them to talk

183
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:47,367
so Wilberto's unfinished
business can finally end.

184
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:49,367
So his soul
can find its way to heaven.

185
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:51,400
Have you seen
Grandma's condition?

186
00:09:51,533 --> 00:09:53,667
This is her second heart attack,

187
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,333
and it's worse now!

188
00:09:56,167 --> 00:09:58,267
She's still unconscious,
so we decided to bring her home.

189
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:01,267
What if she finds out her
brother's bothering her again?

190
00:10:01,433 --> 00:10:02,767
She might have another attack!

191
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,533
Time is precious, Bert.

192
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:07,300
I don't want anything bad
to happen to Miss Nadia

193
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:09,233
before they can reconcile.

194
00:10:09,367 --> 00:10:12,400
Why are you so invested?
What's in it for you?

195
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:13,800
Excuse me?

196
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:15,800
Are you getting money for this?
Will they pay you?

197
00:10:15,933 --> 00:10:17,000
Wow.

198
00:10:17,133 --> 00:10:19,467
Are you thinking?
How can a ghost pay us?

199
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,267
Through Grandma.
I don't know your deal!

200
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,800
That makes no sense!

201
00:10:22,933 --> 00:10:24,633
Your Grandma's upset,

202
00:10:24,767 --> 00:10:27,167
- that's why we need--
- Many have come before you!

203
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:29,067
And they had so many reasons!

204
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,867
I don't care
about those people's deals.

205
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,667
I don't care
how many people came here

206
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,567
or how many you turned away.

207
00:10:35,733 --> 00:10:37,667
The point is,

208
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:41,000
Wilberto never gave up
on your grandmother.

209
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:44,200
That's what matters.

210
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,300
Please, Bert.

211
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,600
I'm worried about Grandma too,

212
00:10:53,633 --> 00:10:55,267
that's why I let you in.

213
00:10:56,267 --> 00:10:58,633
Maybe she needs
to talk to Grandpa Wilberto

214
00:10:58,767 --> 00:10:59,567
before it's too late.

215
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,067
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

216
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:03,300
So, you actually get it.

217
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,167
But...

218
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,033
...just like how you're
following Grandpa's wishes,

219
00:11:09,067 --> 00:11:10,633
I'm also just following
Grandma's wishes.

220
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,733
Tsk.

221
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,100
Bestie.

222
00:11:17,167 --> 00:11:18,100
Here.

223
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,867
Wilberto's gift
to Grandma Nadia.

224
00:11:26,867 --> 00:11:33,900
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

225
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,600
Sit down, man.

226
00:11:54,733 --> 00:11:55,767
How are you?

227
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:57,767
I thought you'd never
come out of that room.

228
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:01,200
Bert's already watching
over her.

229
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,133
It's just sad that...

230
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,967
I can't talk to her
or even touch her.

231
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:10,900
Well, you still can, man.

232
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,233
But...

233
00:12:13,367 --> 00:12:16,433
- only evil spirits can do that.
- [UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,100
And their reason
is usually anger,

235
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:21,467
which is why they're able
to do things that hurt people.

236
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,000
Is that what you want?

237
00:12:23,133 --> 00:12:24,033
Wait.

238
00:12:24,933 --> 00:12:26,800
If Nadia dies full of anger,

239
00:12:27,867 --> 00:12:29,600
that could happen to her, right?

240
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:30,900
Exactly.

241
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:34,267
You know that white lady
on Balete Drive, right?

242
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:38,733
That woman was
full of rage and hatred.

243
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:41,467
That's why she couldn't
cross over to the afterlife.

244
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:46,633
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

245
00:12:46,767 --> 00:12:48,267
You know...

246
00:12:48,433 --> 00:12:50,000
I was just thinking, bro.

247
00:12:51,433 --> 00:12:54,667
Maybe it'll be easier for you
to communicate with Grandma Nads

248
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,867
if you just wait for her to...

249
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,267
...you know.

250
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,167
Are you even thinking, bro?

251
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:04,667
Nadia can't die
without us making peace!

252
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,067
Easy! Easy!

253
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:08,567
I was just laying out
the options, sorry!

254
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:10,567
And then what?
If that happens...

255
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:13,200
she might not cross over and
just turn into an evil spirit.

256
00:13:14,067 --> 00:13:16,067
How can I face
our parents, then?

257
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,567
What do you think
they'll tell me?

258
00:13:18,467 --> 00:13:20,633
That I abandoned her
both in life and in death?

259
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:22,767
- Is that it?
- Okay! Okay!

260
00:13:23,933 --> 00:13:26,000
That's why we need
to convince Bert

261
00:13:26,133 --> 00:13:28,500
to let Jaja and Emma
talk to your sister.

262
00:13:28,633 --> 00:13:30,567
But Nadia's still unconscious.

263
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:32,200
How are we going to talk to her?

264
00:13:34,033 --> 00:13:35,900
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

265
00:13:36,033 --> 00:13:37,567
I've got a story.

266
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:40,633
I had a buddy
who was in a coma, too.

267
00:13:40,767 --> 00:13:42,567
Even though he was unconscious,

268
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:44,667
his wife talked to him
every day.

269
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:45,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

270
00:13:45,967 --> 00:13:47,267
And guess what?

271
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,700
He heard her, man.

272
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:52,300
The body may be asleep,
but the spirit stays awake.

273
00:13:52,433 --> 00:13:53,800
Cool, right?

274
00:13:53,933 --> 00:14:01,000
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

275
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:08,233
[WATER RUNNING]

276
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:14,533
Girl.

277
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:16,933
Oh, yes?

278
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:19,667
Do you think it was
the right decision

279
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:22,100
to leave Treb?

280
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:24,767
Yes, girl.

281
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:29,100
Because if we pushed it,
we might not have made it back.

282
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:31,533
Bert might've reported us.

283
00:14:31,667 --> 00:14:33,300
I don't want that to happen.

284
00:14:34,567 --> 00:14:35,667
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

285
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:36,867
[CLICKS MOUTH]

286
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:42,133
Girl, don't worry
about Treb, okay?

287
00:14:42,767 --> 00:14:44,833
He'll show up.

288
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:46,433
He knows where to find us.

289
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,933
So, you need to rest.

290
00:14:50,067 --> 00:14:51,400
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

291
00:14:51,533 --> 00:14:52,900
You've had a long day.

292
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:54,833
Thank you, girl.

293
00:14:54,967 --> 00:14:56,267
Oh, don't mention it.

294
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,633
- Good night.
- Good night.

295
00:14:58,767 --> 00:15:00,467
Treat me tomorrow!

296
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,833
- When I finally have work.
- [GIGGLES] Okay then.

297
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:10,867
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

298
00:15:37,967 --> 00:15:39,067
Treb?

299
00:15:52,467 --> 00:15:53,367
Treb!

300
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:03,267
How's your sister?

301
00:16:06,167 --> 00:16:07,400
She's still unconscious.

302
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,667
You're not in the 1940s
anymore, Treb.

303
00:16:27,867 --> 00:16:30,500
Men crying isn't a weakness.

304
00:16:31,767 --> 00:16:37,600
[TENDER MUSIC PLAYING]

305
00:16:37,733 --> 00:16:39,533
Jaja, I don't have time to cry.

306
00:16:42,433 --> 00:16:44,633
I might not make it in time.

307
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:53,500
I don't want her to leave
this world full of anger.

308
00:16:56,733 --> 00:16:59,067
What if she can't move on
because she's angry at me?

309
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,367
It's not too late.

310
00:17:02,967 --> 00:17:04,467
What kind of son am I?

311
00:17:05,933 --> 00:17:07,633
What kind of brother?

312
00:17:07,767 --> 00:17:09,433
You did everything you could.

313
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:11,400
[TENDER MUSIC CONTINUES]

314
00:17:11,533 --> 00:17:12,533
Jaja, I'm worthless.

315
00:17:15,033 --> 00:17:16,433
[SOBBING] I'm worthless, Jaja.

316
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:25,467
I'm worthless!
I'm worthless!

317
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:30,600
I'm worthless...

318
00:17:30,733 --> 00:17:32,333
I'm worthless!

319
00:17:35,233 --> 00:17:37,033
I'm worthless, Jaja.

320
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,633
I'm worthless.
I'm worthless!

321
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:49,667
[TENDER MUSIC CONTINUES]

322
00:17:51,267 --> 00:17:53,100
Jaja, I'm worthless.

323
00:17:57,933 --> 00:18:01,267
[SOBBING]

324
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:07,467
That's not true, Treb.

325
00:18:09,933 --> 00:18:11,400
If you were really worthless,

326
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:14,700
then you wouldn't be
doing all of this, would you?

327
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:16,600
[WILBERTO SOBBING]

328
00:18:16,733 --> 00:18:19,700
You didn't stop even
when she pushed you away.

329
00:18:23,767 --> 00:18:24,833
Even when you died,

330
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:27,233
you kept pushing.

331
00:18:28,633 --> 00:18:32,133
Even when it was hard,
you didn't give up.

332
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:37,433
Even when it was impossible,

333
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:40,733
you stood your ground.

334
00:18:47,367 --> 00:18:49,667
And now, you're going
to give up, Treb?

335
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:56,700
["TAYO HANGGANG DULO" BY
FYANG SMITH & JM IBARRA PLAYING]

336
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:35,733
["TAYO HANGGANG DULO" CONTINUES]

337
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:08,600
["TAYO HANGGANG DULO" CONTINUES]

338
00:20:25,567 --> 00:20:27,667
You and your sister
will eventually reconcile.

339
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:28,933
I hope you wake up soon.

340
00:20:30,100 --> 00:20:31,767
Princess...

341
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:35,933
Thank you so much.

342
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,033
Did you tell her about me?

343
00:20:39,167 --> 00:20:40,667
Huh?

344
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:41,767
Oh, that.

345
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:45,500
You see, Nadia used to love it
when I told her stories.

346
00:20:45,633 --> 00:20:47,767
- The princess...
- Me?

347
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:49,100
Princess?

348
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:50,267
Me?

349
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:57,433
["TAYO HANGGANG DULO" CONTINUES]
